description:
Koala Country - Tales from Down Under | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'The Sea Lion King - An Epic Adventure' here: https://youtu.be/498PTmB31wE

The koala bear: a bear that really isn’t a bear. Loved throughout the world as the symbol of Australia, until recently very little was known about this marsupial. Once thought of only as the sleepy creature residing in Eucalyptus trees, research now paints a different picture. 

Koala Country is the story of one young male koala from his birth to the time when he becomes the dominant male of a patch of eucalyptus forest. During his journey, he must overcome the obstacles that have always been a part of a koala’s life. There are natural predators, such as pythons and owls, that easily could take a joey (baby koala).  

Koalas must survive the extremes of the climate, from winter storms to searing heat and drought causing wildfires that have been a part of the Australian ecosystem for millions of years.
